Name: findAngleY

Type: function

Syntax: findAngleY(x1,y1,x2,y2)

Summary: returns the center angle of a circle in degrees. x1,y1 are the coordinates of the center point of the circle. x2,y2 are the coordinates of a

Example: get findAngleY(100,200,50,300)

Example: get findAngleY(the loc of grc 1,the loc of grc 2)

Description:
returns the center angle of a circle in degrees. x1,y1 are the coordinates of the center point of the circle. x2,y2 are the coordinates of a point on the circular arc. Possible values are 0-360, where 0 degrees means x2,y2 being on top of x1,y1.

This function can be used as a synony for findAngle()



