Name: constrainElliptical

Type: property

Syntax: constrainElliptical centerX,centerY,radiusX,radiusY

Summary: Allows dragging a control on an ellipse. The control can not be dragged outside of that ellipse

Example: set the constrainElliptical of btn "yourButton" to 100,100,50,100

Description:
Allows dragging a control on an ellipse. The control can not be dragged outside of that ellipse.

Attention! You need to make sure that the following messages are not trapped in the target control:

mouseDown, mouseUp, mouseRelease, mouseMove. If you need to use these messages make sure that you pass them.

New in 2.0:

You might use the following messages instead to avoid conflicts:

mouseDown    - constrainEllipticalInit

mouseUp         - constrainEllipticalExit

mouseRelease  - constrainEllipticalExit

mouseMove     - constrainEllipticalCallback



