Summary: Use this handler to change the speed of a circular moving control with an ease in and out effect. You pass the following parameters:

Example: send "moveCircularEaseInOut 2,1000,4" to btn "myCircularMovingButton"

Example: send "moveCircularEaseInOut 0,1500" to grc "myCircularMovingGraphic"

Description:
Use this handler to change the speed of a circular moving control with an ease in and out effect. You pass the following parameters:

newStep - the new value for the moveCircular["step"] of the control

duration  - the duration of the ease effect in milliseconds

exponent - optional parameter to achieve cubic, quadric or other easing



Name: constrainCircular

Type: property

Syntax: constrainCircular centerX,centerY,radius

Summary: Allows dragging a control on a circle. The control can not be dragged outside of that circle

Example: set the constrainCircular of btn "yourButton" to 100,100,50

Description:
Allows dragging a control on a circle. The control can not be dragged outside of that circle.

Attention! You need to make sure that the following messages are not trapped in the target control:

mouseDown, mouseUp, mouseRelease, mouseMove. If you need to use these messages make sure that you pass them.

New in 2.0:

You might use the following messages instead to avoid conflicts:

mouseDown    - constrainCircularInit

mouseUp         - constrainCircularExit

mouseRelease  - constrainCircularExit

mouseMove     - constrainCircularCallback



