Type: function

Syntax: circleLineSegmentCollide(x1,y1,x2,y2,x3,y3,radius)

Summary: This function returns true if there is a collision between a line segment (specified by startpoint x1,y1 and the endpoint x2,y2 and a circle

Example: get circleLineSegmentCollide(100,200,200,250,80,80,40)

Example: get circleLineSegmentCollide(line 1 of the points of grc "line",line 2 of the points of grc "line",the loc of img "circle",40)

Description:
This function returns true if there is a collision between a line segment (specified by startpoint x1,y1 and the endpoint x2,y2 and a circle (specified by the circles centerpoint x3,y3 and it´s radius). Else it returns false.



Name: isoToScreenX

Type: function

Syntax: isoToScreenX(x,y,z,originX)

Summary: This function returns the x component of a 3D point converted to screen coordinates in isometric view. It is needed by the isoToScreen funct

Example: get isoToScreenX(100,200,20,200)

Description:
This function returns the x component of a 3D point converted to screen coordinates in isometric view. It is needed by the isoToScreen function. Returned values are not rounded.



Name: constrainRectangular

Type: property

Syntax: constrainRectangular left,top,right,bottom

Summary: Allows a drag of a control in a rectangle specified by left,top,right,bottom. The control can not be dragged outside of that rectangle. The 

Example: set the constrainRectangular of btn "myButton" to 100,100,250,300

Example: set the constrainRectangular of btn "myButton" to the rect of grc "test"

Description:
Allows a drag of a control in a rectangle specified by left,top,right,bottom. The control can not be dragged outside of that rectangle. The first variant of that script has been posted to the use-revolution list by Scott Rossi.

Attention! You need to make sure that the following messages are not trapped in the target control:

mouseDown, mouseUp, mouseRelease, mouseMove. If you need to use these messages make sure that you pass them.

New in 2.0:

You might use the following messages instead to avoid conflicts:

mouseDown    - constrainRectangularInit

mouseUp         - constrainRectangularExit

mouseRelease  - constrainRectangularExit

mouseMove     - constrainRectangularCallback



