Description:
Use this handler to change the speed of an elliptical moving control with an ease in and out effect. You pass the following parameters:

newStep - the new value for the moveElliptical["step"] of the control

duration  - the duration of the ease effect in milliseconds

exponent - optional parameter to achieve cubic, quadric or other easing
aspectResize
ratio
1.666667
example
pointInPoly
^
About the pointInpoly example

In this example you can drag a polygon graphic or a button. If the location of the button is within the polyGon the the icon of the button changes.

Steps necessary to create this demo:

Step 1

Draw 2 icons for the button in your favourite image editor.

Step 2

Create a stack with a freehand polygon graphic, Set the name of it to "pipPoly". Create a button. Set the name of it to "pipBut". Import the images. Set the names of them to "myImage1" and "myImage2"

Step 3

In the messagebox do the following:

Step 4

Apply the following script to the graphic and the button:

moveCircular
2
About the moveCircular example

The following steps were necessary to create the demo (simplified)

Step 1

Create a stack with an oval graphic, 2 buttons and 4 sliders. Set the name of the graphic to "moveCircularPath". Set the names of the buttons to "cBall" and "animate". Set the values of the sliders to the following:

Slider 1: startValue 100 endValue 300

Slider 2: startValue 100 endValue 300

Slider 3: startValue 0     endValue 100

Slider 4: startValue 0     endValue 10

Step 2

Apply the following scripts:

Button "animate"

Slider 1:

Slider 2:

Slider 3:

Slider 4:

Step 3

Drag all sliders and hit the "animate" button

ae3dConvertToScreen
midLeft
constrainLinear

About the constrainElliptical demo

In this demo you can drag a ball on a linear path.

The following steps were necessary to create this demo.

Step 1

Draw two ball images in an image editor of your choice.

Step 2

Create a stack, import the images. Set the names of the images to "myImage1" and "myImage2"Create a line graphic and a button. Set the name of the graphic to "myGraphic" and the name of the button to "linearDrag".

Step 3

In the messagebox do the following:

The actual dragging is already set now. switch to the browse tool and try it.

Step 4

To improve the feel you can apply the following script to the button "circleDrag"

moveCircularReversePath
findPreciseAngle

About the findPreciseAngle example

In this example you can drag any of the two balls and get some visual feedback on the center angle.

Steps that were necessaryto create this demo:

Step 1

Draw two ball images in your favourite image editor

Step 2

Create a stack. Create 2 oval graphics. Set the name of the first graphic to "angleDisplay2" set the name of the second graphic to "angleDisplay". Create 2 line graphics. Set the names of them to "angleLine1" and "angleLine2". Import the images you created. Set the names of them to "findAngle1" and "findAngle2". Create a field and set its name to "angleDisplay"

Step 3

